# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# E2E TEST ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# This file is a template for .env.test which contains actual credentials
# for the E2E test environment.
#
# IMPORTANT: .env.test should be in .gitignore and never committed!
#
# Setup:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.test
# 2. Fill in the actual values from your test Supabase project
# 3. Ensure the E2E test user exists in your test database
#
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Test Database (Supabase)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# URL to your TEST Supabase project
# Format: https://[project-ref].supabase.co
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-test-project.supabase.co

# Public anon key for your TEST Supabase project
# Get this from: Supabase Dashboard > Settings > API > Project API keys > anon public
SUPABASE_PUBLIC_KEY=your-test-anon-public-key-here

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Dedicated E2E Test User
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This user should already exist in your test database
# Create it manually in Supabase Auth or via migration script

# User ID (UUID from auth.users table)
E2E_USERNAME_ID=00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

# User email
E2E_USERNAME=e2e-test-user@adoptme-test.pl

# User password (make it strong but memorable for test purposes)
E2E_PASSWORD=TestPassword123!

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Notes
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Why a dedicated E2E user?
# - Faster test execution (no need to create/delete users)
# - More reliable tests (user always exists)
# - Easier debugging (consistent user ID across test runs)
# - Cleaner test database (no orphaned test users)
#
# How to create the E2E test user in Supabase:
# 1. Go to: Supabase Dashboard > Authentication > Users
# 2. Click "Add user" > "Create new user"
# 3. Enter the email and password from above
# 4. Confirm the user's email (toggle "Email confirmed")
# 5. Copy the user's UUID to E2E_USERNAME_ID
#
# Alternative: Use a migration script to create the user programmatically
#
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
